A [[Pattern Language]] for collaborative practices. The key difference between a pattern language and a framework is that you only apply a pattern when you actually need it - when it addresses a challenge or a risk you're actually experiencing.

Pattern languages have long been associated with Agile. Prominent examples include the original {{XP}} and {{Scrum}} pattern languages, 